
'''聖典'''是许多[[宗教|宗教中]]出现的一个[[神學|神学]]术语。它被[[定义|定义]]为神圣的影响力<ref>{{Cite book|last=Blackmore, R. D. (Richard Doddridge), 1825-1900.|url=http://worldcat.org/oclc/1084383140|title=Lorna Doone|date=[19--?]|publisher=Ryerson Press|isbn=0-665-26503-4|oclc=1084383140}}</ref> 。它以再生、圣化、激发良善的冲动，并赋予力量以经受审判和抵抗诱惑。 <ref>''OED'', 2nd ed.: grace(n), 11b</ref>并且作为神圣起源的个人美德或卓越。 <ref>''OED'', 2nd ed.: grace(n), 11e</ref>

== 佛教 ==
虽然[[佛教派别|佛教]]中许多[[佛教派别|流派]]都强调自律和努力是[[涅槃_(佛教)|开悟]]的途径，但也存在一些恩典的概念。最著名的例子是[[淨土宗|净土宗]]和[[淨土真宗|淨土真宗]]的教义，该教义由12世纪的日本和尚[[親鸞|親鸞]][[親鸞|創立]]。在佛教中， [[福德_(佛教)|福德]]的概念是指通过冥想和精神修养而得，並且随着时间的流逝可累積[[業|善业]]。當善業達到一定程度時，建基同情並達到菩提心時可把善業用來幫助其他众生。对于Shinran而言，几乎所有人都缺乏这种自我指导的精神修养的能力，或者是在妄想和自私的海洋中迷失的生物，這代表著良好的行为會漸漸受到自私的污染。這修練方式除了依靠自力外，亦需要[[信仰|堅信不疑]]擁抱“神聖力量”，这就是[[阿弥陀佛|阿彌佛陀]]。无数千年以前，他培養足够的福德建立[[淨土|淨土]]。並[[本愿|发願]]要拯救所有的众生，只要通过稱呼他的名字就可以使他们往生淨土，并在當中轻松地成佛。Shinran的学說其他净土宗之间的主要区别在于，如果没有阿彌陀佛陀聖典的帮助，即使不斷[[念佛|念佛]]也是不可能的发願。因此，念佛更多地是为了表达对已经存在的恩典的感激之情，而不是自我诱导尚未出现的恩典催化剂。 <ref>{{Cite web |url=http://bschawaii.org/shindharmanet/bloom/ab-writings/amazing/ |title=存档副本 |access-date=2020-10-01 |archive-date=2020-08-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200805082754/http://bschawaii.org/shindharmanet/bloom/ab-writings/amazing/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 基督教 ==
{{Main|恩典}}

基督教中的恩典是[[基督教的神|上帝]]給予於应得的[[wiktionary:favor|恩惠]]，这在[[基督教救贖論|基督教救贖論]]和祝福的恩赐中得到体现。<ref>''OED'', 2nd ed.: grace(n), 11a</ref>基督教的普遍教义就是上帝的恩典，這是上帝赋予人类的慈悲，並使他的[[聖子|聖子]][[耶稣|耶稣基督]][[耶穌被釘十字架|被釘十字架上]]，从而使人永远得救。

在[[基督宗教|基督宗教]]，关于如何获得恩典存在不同的概念。特别是，[[天主教|天主教]]和[[新教|新教]]以不同的方式理解恩典。它被描述为“将[[天主教會|天主教]]与[[新教|新教]]、[[加爾文主義|加尔文主义]]与[[阿民念主義|阿民念主义]]、现代自由主义与保守主义的分水岭”。 <ref>Charles C. Ryrie, ''The Grace of God'' (Chicago: Moody Press, 1963), pp. 10-11.</ref>天主教教义教导说，上帝赋予了人类神圣的恩典，并进行了[[聖禮|圣礼]]<ref>{{Cite book|title=[[Catechism_of_the_Catholic_Church|Catechism of the Catholic Church]] No. 1127|location=Vatican City-State|quote=Celebrated worthily in faith, the sacraments confer the grace that they signify.}}</ref>作为接受他的恩典的主要有效手段。 <ref>http://www.saintaquinas.com/Justification_by_Grace {{Wayback|url=http://www.saintaquinas.com/Justification_by_Grace |date=20170630233632 }}. html</ref>对天主教徒而言，[[聖禮|圣礼]]是神的恩典通过肉体化的有形手段获得，他的恩典成为个人和生存的接受。 <ref>[[Edward_Schillebeeckx|Edward Schillebeeckx]], ''Christ, the Sacrament of Encounter with God'' (Rowman & Littlefield, 1963), Foreword pp. 16</ref>一般而言，新教徒不同意这种恩典传播的观点， <ref>{{Cite web|title=Archived copy|url=http://www.experiencefestival.com/a/Heaven_-_Heaven_in_Protestant_Christianity/id/1292134|accessdate=2010-12-14|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091124002753/http://www.experiencefestival.com/a/Heaven_-_Heaven_in_Protestant_Christianity/id/1292134|archivedate=2009-11-24}}</ref>而是赞成一种制度化程度较低的机制。例如，在天主教会中，上帝通过洗礼<ref>{{Cite book|title=[[Catechism_of_the_Catholic_Church|Catechism of the Catholic Church]] No. 1992|location=Vatican City-State|quote=Justification is conferred in Baptism, the sacrament of faith.}}</ref>而不是简单的信仰祈祷来给予恩典。但是，天主教徒不会否认即使是简单的祈祷也能使上帝的恩典得以传播，但這是歸屬於[[欲望的洗礼|欲望的洗禮]]<ref>{{Cite book|title=[[Catechism_of_the_Catholic_Church|Catechism of the Catholic Church]] No. 1260|location=Vatican City-State}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title=[[Catechism_of_the_Catholic_Church|Catechism of the Catholic Church]] No. 1281|location=Vatican City-State|quote=... those who ... seek God sincerely and strive to fulfill his will, are saved even if they have not been baptized.}}</ref>。

另一个例子，对于天主教徒来说，和解圣礼是在犯下致命罪后传递恩典的主要手段。 <ref>{{Cite book|title=[[Catechism_of_the_Catholic_Church|Catechism of the Catholic Church]] No. 1446|location=The Vatican|quote=Christ instituted the sacrament of Penance for all sinful members of his Church: above all for those who, since Baptism, have fallen into grave sin, and have thus lost their baptismal grace and wounded ecclesial communion. It is to them that the sacrament of Penance offers a new possibility to convert and to recover the grace of justification. The Fathers of the Church present this sacrament as "the second plank [of salvation] after the shipwreck which is the loss of grace."}}</ref>历史上有许多恩典与[[玫瑰经|念珠]]的祈祷有关;多米尼加人的传统也报道了圣母玛利亚对圣多米尼克和艾伦·德·鲁佩（Alan de Rupe）的十五个念珠诺言，信奉虔诚祈祷念珠的基督徒。

=== 經文的解說 ===
在[[新約聖經|新约圣经]]中，希腊语Charis''（'' {{IPAc-en|ˈ|k|eɪ|r|ɪ|s}} ;{{Lang-grc|[[Wiktionary:χάρις|χάρις]]}}  ）可译为恩典。为此，斯特朗给出了以下定义：“礼貌、举止和行为。 <ref>{{Cite web|title=Strong's Greek: 5485. χάρις (charis) -- grace, kindness|url=http://strongsnumbers.com/greek/5485.htm|work=strongsnumbers.com|access-date=2020-10-01|archive-date=2011-09-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110902085532/http://strongsnumbers.com/greek/5485.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref>Strong (2001) Grk entry number 5485 (p. 1653)</ref>来自“家庭恩典”的一词是属灵恩赐，在《新圣经词典》中則被定义为“恩典是在言行上产生明显影响”。 <ref>{{Cite web|title=Spiritual Gifts: Listed by Paul, Motivated by Love|url=https://www.crosswalk.com/faith/spiritual-life/spiritual-gifts-listed-by-paul-motivated-by-love.html|access-date=2020-10-01|archive-date=2021-02-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213220939/https://www.crosswalk.com/faith/spiritual-life/spiritual-gifts-listed-by-paul-motivated-by-love.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>与charis相关的希腊语单词是charisma 。这两个词都源自另一个希腊词chairo。 <ref>Strong (2001) Grk entry numbers 5486 and 5463</ref>

在[[旧约圣经|旧约]]中，[[希伯来语|希伯来语]]的恩典是chen <ref>{{Citation|url=http://www.blueletterbible.org/lang/lexicon/lexicon.cfm?Strongs=H02580&Version=kjv|title=Blue Letter Bible entry for Strongs Hebrew term 2580|publisher=[[Blue_Letter_Bible|Blue Letter Bible]] institute|access-date=2011-01-01|archive-date=2017-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170707213656/https://www.blueletterbible.org/lang/lexicon/lexicon.cfm?Strongs=H02580&Version=kjv|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|title=Chen - Old Testament Hebrew Lexicon - New American Standard|url=http://www.biblestudytools.com/lexicons/hebrew/nas/chen.html|work=Bible Study Tools|access-date=2020-10-01|archive-date=2020-11-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201126154652/https://www.biblestudytools.com/lexicons/hebrew/nas/chen.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>代表了仁慈的道德品质，显示了良好的行為”。 <ref>Strong (2001) Hebrew entry number 2580 (p. 1501)</ref>在詹姆士的译本中，chen被译成“恩典” 38次、“被宠爱” 26次、“亲切”两次。 <ref>Proverbs 11:16 and Ecclesiastes 9:11</ref>也有被译成“令人愉悦” <ref>Proverbs 5:19</ref> 和“珍贵”。 <ref>Proverbs 17:8</ref>

== 印度教 ==
遍布印度和尼泊尔的印度教或[[巴克蒂|巴克蒂]]文献都有着聖典的解說，這可作为灵性自我实现所需的最终关键。<ref>[http://www.hindu.com/2005/06/30/stories/2005063000400900.htm Descent of divine grace] {{Wayback|url=http://www.hindu.com/2005/06/30/stories/2005063000400900.htm |date=20060512000536 }} ''[[The_Hindu|The Hindu]]'', June 30, 2005.</ref>例如古老的贤者瓦西莎在他的经典著作《瑜伽瓦西莎》中，认为这是超越[[業|业力]]的束缚唯一途径。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Yoga Vasistha - Daily Readings - Swami Venkatesananda|url=http://www.venkatesaya.com/241_vasistha01_months_tags/index.vasistha01_months_tags.php?m=12&d=27|author=venkatesananda|first=|work=www.venkatesaya.com|access-date=2020-10-01|archive-date=2013-04-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130402210124/http://www.venkatesaya.com/241_vasistha01_months_tags/index.vasistha01_months_tags.php?m=12&d=27|dead-url=no}}</ref>一个印度教哲学家马德瓦查里亚认为，聖典不是上帝的恩赐，而是必须获得的。 <ref>''Great Thinkers of the Eastern World'', Ian McGreal.</ref>

== 伊斯兰教 ==
[[萨拉菲运动|薩拉菲運動]]學者奥马尔·苏莱曼和伊斯兰法学院院长在[[扎卡私人大学|扎尔卡大學]]写道：“天堂是擁有巨大价值的东西，一个人不能凭借他的事迹獲得，而是由格雷斯和真主的怜悯。” <ref>{{Citation|url=http://www.call-to-monotheism.com/answering_common_questions_on_salvation_that_christians_pose_to_muslims|title=Answering Common Questions on Salvation That Christians Pose to Muslims|last=Bassam Zawadi|last2=Mansur Ahmed|access-date=2011-01-01|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112042527/https://www.call-to-monotheism.com/answering_common_questions_on_salvation_that_christians_pose_to_muslims|dead-url=no}}</ref>这种立场得到[[聖訓|圣训]]支持。根据阿布·赫拉拉的说法，先知穆罕默德曾说过：“你们之中，没有一个人可以仅凭他的行径进入天堂……甚至我都不行，但相信安拉會以他的恩典和怜悯我們。 ” <ref>{{Citation|title=Sahih Muslim, Book 39|chapter=Chapter 15: None Would Attain Salvation Because of his Deeds but it is Through Lord's Mercy, Number 6764|publisher=University of Southern California center for Jewish-Muslim engagement|url=http://www.usc.edu/schools/college/crcc/engagement/resources/texts/muslim/hadith/muslim/039.smt.html|access-date=2011-01-01|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110102202428/http://www.usc.edu/schools/college/crcc/engagement/resources/texts/muslim/hadith/muslim/039.smt.html|archivedate=2011-01-02}}</ref>
